{
  "stem": "14060.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "These people didn't even speak German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, I as a child spoke better German than Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Obviously I went to Hungarian schools, so that wore off a little bit and probably my grammar is better in Hungarian than in German.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But today I don't know, maybe probably in English.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that area, these people, was not too advisable for Jews to communicate.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Far as I know, that my father spoke the dialect, which was a-- a different German dialect than the normal [NON-ENGLISH] German, normal German, which is spoken, and traded with them.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But at the same time, they were vehemently anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The-- I remember that in 1941, at a later point, there was a whole SS brigade or battalion put together from volunteers of the sons of these people.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The-- I watched a year later the Red Cross trains bringing them back injured, and some mutilated, from the Russian front.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nevertheless, the-- the-- the hatred against Jews was constantly if not on top of the surface, certainly under it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, the interesting period of my schooling time is also that I finished my primary school in the summer of 1940.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was supposed to start school in September.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Those days in this gymnasium, there was also another lyceum, which was a Protestant grammar school.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then there was the [NON-ENGLISH], they called them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was the Catholic priests school, also a secular school, but it was run by priests.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then there was the-- what you could call in England the comprehensive school, where all of the people who were not academically really up to it went for four years and that was the end of their education.",
      "word_count": 39
    }
  ],
